<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="238" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Calhoun</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-18"><hi rend="italic">April 18,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Knox informs Mr. Calhoun that the following telegram has to-day been
                            sent to the American embassy at St. Petersburg:<note n="1" xml:id="d238fn1">Telegram of Apr. 18 supra.</note></p>
                        <p>Mr. Knox states that Mr. Calhoun may read this telegram to the minister
                            for foreign affairs for his information. Directs that the telegram be
                            repeated to the American embassy at Tokyo.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>